solution: ```class Solution {
    public int rangeBitwiseAnd(int left, int right) {
        while (right > left) {
            right &= right - 1;
        }
        return right;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Repeatedly clears the lowest set bit of `right` until `right` equals `left`; the remaining common prefix is the bitwise AND of the entire range.

